      <p>
        Natura11y is independent, open source, and shaped by the kind of work small teams actually do: building useful websites with limited time, real content, real users, and real accessibility responsibilities.
      </p>

      <p>
        It is not trying to lock teams into a product suite or a single way of working. The priorities are simpler: readable HTML, flexible adoption, useful examples, and accessible components that keep working after a site is handed off.
      </p>

      <a class="button theme-primary" href="/docs/customization/">
        <span class="text">Avidano Digital</span>
        <span class="icon icon-open-new" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </a>

    </div>

  </section>

  <section>

    <div class="backdrop">

      <div class="backdrop__media">
        <Image
          class="opacity-40 gradient-mask-bottom"
          src={pronunciationImage}
          alt=""
          widths={[640, 960, 1280, 1600, 2000]}
          sizes="100vw"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="backdrop__cover justify-content-end margin-y-5">

        <div class="container medium--md">

          <h2 class="banner-headline text-align-center text-shadow--lg">
            Natura11y is pronounced naturally (natch-er-uh-lee)
          </h2>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
      
